org.agilewiki.jactor2.core.util.immutable

Class HashTreePProperties<VALUE>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.agilewiki.jactor2.core.util.immutable.HashTreePProperties<VALUE>
  • Type Parameters:
    VALUE - The type of value.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Map<java.lang.String,VALUE>, ImmutableProperties<VALUE>

    public class HashTreePProperties<VALUE>
extends java.lang.Object
implements ImmutableProperties<VALUE>

    An implementation of ImmutableProperties based on pcollections. 

     Sample:

 public class HashTreePPropertiesSample {
     public static void main(final String[] args) {
         ImmutableProperties<String> ip = HashTreePProperties.empty();
         ip = ip.plus("one", "1");
         ip = ip.plus("two", "2");
         ImmutableProperties<String> ip2 = ip;
         ip = ip.plus("three", "3");
         System.out.println(ip2.sortedKeySet());
         System.out.println(ip.subMap("t").sortedKeySet());
     }
 }

 Output:

 [one, two]
 [three, two]
